\begin_layout Standard
The EUR to DKK rate is pegged by Denmark at 7.46 and is required to deviate no more than 2.25% from this value.
 We may model the log-exchange rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln X_{t}$
\end_inset

 as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
d\ln X_{t}=-\theta\left(\ln X_{t}-\mu\right)dt+\sigma dW_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
dX_{t} & =de^{\ln X_{t}}\\
 & =e^{\ln X_{t}}\left(d\ln X_{t}\right)+\frac{1}{2}e^{\ln X_{t}}\left(d\ln X_{t}\right)^{2}\\
 & =X_{t}\left[-\theta\left(\ln X_{t}-\mu\right)dt+\sigma dW_{t}\right]+\frac{X_{t}}{2}\sigma^{2}dt
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y_{t}=\ln X_{t}-\mu
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
such that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
dY_{t} & =-\theta\left(\ln X_{t}-\mu\right)dt+\sigma dW_{t}\\
 & =-\theta Y_{t}dt+\sigma dW_{t}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Solving this SDE gives
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y_{t}=Y_{0}e^{-\theta t}+\sigma\intop_{0}^{t}e^{\theta(s-t)}dW_{s}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's say the total value of our s-elf-financing portfolio at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}$
\end_inset

,
 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{t}=C_{t}+X_{t}U_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{t}$
\end_inset

 are the amount of cash and the number of DKK/EUR that we hold at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

.
 Of course,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dV_{t}=dC_{t}+X_{t}dU_{t}+U_{t}dX_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the portfolio is self-financing,
 
\begin_inset Formula $dC_{t}+X_{t}dU_{t}=0$
\end_inset

.
 Let
\begin_inset Formula $U_{t}=\frac{V_{t}h\left(Y_{t}\right)}{X_{t}}$
\end_inset

.
 Then
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
dV_{t} & =\frac{V_{t}h(Y_{t})}{X_{t}}dX_{t}\\
 & =V_{t}h\left(Y_{t}\right)\left[-\theta\left(\ln X_{t}-\mu\right)dt+\sigma dW_{t}+\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2}dt\right]\\
 & =V_{t}h\left(Y_{t}\right)\left[\left(-\theta Y_{t}+\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2}\right)dt+\sigma dW_{t}\right]\\
